name: Consistent Care Services- COVID Vaccine Site
vaccines: Janssen COVID-19 Vaccine, Pfizer-BioNTech COVID-19 Vaccine
info:
***The first 20 registered patients at this clinic will receive a $50 Visa gift card that can be used anywhere Visa is accepted.*** You will need to agree to record your name and # at the clinic verifying you received the gift card.  This is a clinic for 1st or 2nd doses of the Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine or the single dose of the Johnson & Johnson*** All patients 12 years old and older can register for the Pfizer vaccine only. (If 12-17 years old for the Pfizer vaccine, you must be with a parent or guardian or have parental/guardian consent)  The clinic is located at the Hillyard library at 4005 N. Cook St. 
***Residents of ANY state are now eligible for the vaccine, but you still must have photo ID***
*VERY IMPORTANT*
***Please complete all the insurance/Medicare/Medicaid information when registering online for your appointment to avoid filling it out at the clinic***
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Olympic Pharmacy and Healthcare Services - COVID Vaccine Venue
address: 4700 Pt Fosdick Dr, Suite 120, Gig Harbor Washington, 98335
info:
**THIS CLINIC IS FOR JANSSEN (JOHNSON&JOHNSON) VACCINATION ONLY**

You must be 18 years of age or older.
Please bring your State ID, and if you have insurance, please bring your insurance card or Medicare B card (red,white and blue card).
Please do not come to the clinic if you are not feeling well.
Please wear loose sleeved, short sleeved or sleeveless shirt
When you enter Olympic Pharmacy, please follow COVID clinic signs to the back conference/fitting area. This clinic is not in the pharmacy area.
Please arrive as close as possible to your scheduled time to prevent crowding that will impede appropriate social distancing.
Please be prepared to wait 15-30 minutes after vaccination for observation of adverse reactions.
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.
